# Local check before push

**Plain English:** Finish the slice locally, give **How to check locally**, and **wait**. Do not push until owner says **push**, **ship it**, or **go live**.

## Workflow

| Step | Agent | Owner |
|------|-------|-------|
| 1 | Make changes locally | — |
| 2 | Say **Local only (not pushed yet)** | — |
| 3 | Give numbered check steps (`npx serve . -l 3000`) | Clicks through |
| 4 | Owner says looks good / ship it | Confirms |
| 5 | Commit + push (if asked) | Optional check on live Vercel URL |

## Status wording

| State | Say |
|-------|-----|
| Built, not pushed | **Local only (not pushed yet).** |
| After push | **Live deploy in progress (pushed to main; Vercel building).** |
| Deploy done | **Live on mactech-gear.vercel.app** (or mactechgear.ca when DNS is cut). |

## Never commit

`.env`, `.env.local`, secrets, Vercel tokens
